# Proxy 46 — Protocol-translating proxy → Proxy A (IPv6 upstream)
#
# Listens on port 80 on both IPv4 (10.72.39.166) and IPv6 ([fd00:72:39:0:A600::166]).
# Always forwards to Proxy A's IPv6 address regardless of the incoming protocol.
#
# Use case: test IPv4-to-IPv6 conversion.
#   - Connect via IPv4: http://10.72.39.166/
#     The request arrives over IPv4 but is forwarded to Proxy A over IPv6.
#     The Forwarded header will show the IPv4 client address, but REMOTE_ADDR
#     at WordPress will be Proxy A's IPv6 address (fd00:72:39:0:8000::128).

:80 {
	reverse_proxy [fd00:72:39:0:8000::128]:80 {
		header_up +Forwarded "for={http.request.remote.host};proto={http.request.scheme};host={http.request.host}"
	}
}
